the font format is pretty specific so comments aren't allowed
everywhere but you can have them at the start, which is good
for credits and attributions. we use .rgft here but as usual
a couple letters tacked onto the end of a file name doesn't
mean anything we aren't your microslop
first content should be two decimal numbers delimited by an x
and nothing else to indicate the dimensions of the font (width
by height) then in any order specify any number of 
- alphabet_upper
- alphabet_lower
- special
- special2
- special3
to specify ascii regions 65-90,97-122,33-64,91-96, and 123-126
respectively & inclusively, followed by all characters in that
block adjacent to each other as the author would like rendered
if the sequence had been inputted.
if the width of the font (first number) is 0, then after each
region specifier and before the letters, there should be a
line of spaces with periods wherever a character ends. this
allows variable-width characters (non-monospace). there is not
yet support for variable-height characters. might make a way
to port figlet fonts later because that's where i've been
stealing from. save me public domain.
